Q.1. Who is the author of this article ?
(A) Anton Chekov
(B) John Galsworthy
(C) Katherine Mansfield
(D) Binapani Mohanti

Answer: (B) John Galsworthy
Explanation: The lesson “Quality” is written by John Galsworthy.

Q.2. Who was Mr. Gessler ?
(A) A goldsmith
(B) A Carpenter
(C) A shoe maker
(D) A farmer

Answer: (C) A shoe maker
Explanation: Mr. Gessler was a shoemaker who made high-quality boots.

Q.3. How did the author know him ?
(A) As an artist
(B) As a professional shoe trader
(C) As a commercial artist
(D) None of these

Answer: (A) As an artist
Explanation: The author knew Mr. Gessler as a bootmaker who treated his work as art.

Q.4. What was the author’s opinion about Mr. Gessler as a shoemaker ?
(A) Man of good nature
(B) Good as heart and hard mind
(C) Jealous in nature
(D) All of the above

Answer: (B) Good as heart and hard mind
Explanation: The author thought Mr. Gessler was dedicated and serious about his work.

Q.5. Mr. Gessler was not successful in his trade, why ?
(A) He was a true shoe-maker but not a true businessman
(B) He was not in favour of new developments
(C) He avoided to adopt new techniques
(D) All

Answer: (D) All
Explanation: He was a good craftsman but not a businessman and did not adopt modern methods.

Q.6. Mr. Gessler was a……………….bootmaker.
(A) Russian
(B) German
(C) French
(D) English

Answer: (B) German
Explanation: Mr. Gessler was a German bootmaker in London.

Q.7. For Mr. Gessler, bootmaking was a/an
(A) Art
(B) Burden
(C) Job
(D) Timepass

Answer: (A) Art
Explanation: He considered bootmaking an art, not just a job.

Q.8. Mr. Gessler blamed the big firms for taking away the livelihood of…………….. like himself who worked on a low scale.
(A) Shopkeepers
(B) Landowners
(C) Bearers
(D) Workers

Answer: (D) Workers
Explanation: Big firms affected small workers like Mr. Gessler.

Q.9. When the author visited Mr. Gessler’s shop after a gap of nearly two years, he found another…………………name also painted on one of the windows of the shop.
(A) Bootmaker’s
(B) Baker’s
(C) Florist’s
(D) Plumber’s

Answer: (A) Bootmaker’s
Explanation: Another bootmaker’s name was written, showing business decline.

Q.10. The young man admitted that Mr. Gessler was the best bootmaker in
(A) Berlin
(B) Tokyo
(C) London
(D) Paris

Answer: (C) London
Explanation: Mr. Gessler was considered the best bootmaker in London.

Q.11. According to Mr. Gessler, big firms have no
(A) money
(B) manner
(C) interest
(D) self-respect

Answer: (D) self-respect
Explanation: He believed big firms cared only for money, not quality.

Q.12. ‘The Island Pharisees’ was the important work of
(A) Premchand
(B) Anton Chekov
(C) John Galsworthy
(D) Katherine Mansfield

Answer: (C) John Galsworthy
Explanation: “The Island Pharisees” is a work by John Galsworthy.

Q.13. How many assistant Mr. Gessler keep to assist him in his work?
(A) One
(B) Two
(C) Three
(D) None

Answer: (D) None
Explanation: He worked alone and had no assistants.

Q.14. Mr. Gessler made…………….boots.
(A) bad
(B) kind
(C) old
(D) good

Answer: (D) good
Explanation: He made very good quality boots.

Q.15. Mr. Gessler advertised his trade.
(A) True
(B) False
(C) Sometimes
(D) None of these

Answer: (B) False
Explanation: He never advertised; he believed in quality work.

Q.16. According to the doctor, Mr. Gessler had died of
(A) food
(B) bad food
(C) slow-starvation
(D) None of these

Answer: (C) slow-starvation
Explanation: He died because he spent all money on leather and rent and did not eat properly.

Q.17. Whatever Mr. Gessler earned was spent in
(A) Roti and dal
(B) bread and butter
(C) rent and leather
(D) shoes and boots

Answer: (C) rent and leather
Explanation: He spent money on rent and leather for boots.

Q.18. Once the author went into Mr. Gessler’s shop in a pair of boots bought at some large
(A) art
(B) firm
(C) town
(D) bank

Answer: (B) firm
Explanation: The author once bought boots from a big firm.

Q.19. Why did Mr. Gessler die?
(A) due to his diseases
(B) due to slow – starvation
(C) due to oldness
(D) none of these

Answer: (B) due to slow – starvation
Explanation: He died due to slow starvation because of poverty.

Q.20. John Galsworthy was born in
(A) 1867
(B) 1857
(C) 1847
(D) 1876

Answer: (A) 1867
Explanation: John Galsworthy was born in 1867.

Q.21. John Galsworthy was died in ………………
(A) 1923
(B) 1933
(C) 1934
(D) 1924

Answer: (B) 1933
Explanation: He died in 1933.

Q.22. Mr. Gessler’s shop was situated in…………….
(A) Yorkshire
(B) the West End
(C) Canaught Place
(D) Part street

Answer: (B) the West End
Explanation: His shop was in the West End of London.

Q.23. Mr. Gessler’s shop was known by the name of ……………
(A) Gessler Boots
(B) Quality Boots
(C) Gessler Brothers
(D) None of these

Answer: (C) Gessler Brothers
Explanation: The shop was named Gessler Brothers.
